    { q: "What is the primary architectural difference between HTTP and WebSockets?", options: ["WebSockets are entirely offline", "HTTP is mathematically unidirectional (client requests, server responds); WebSockets create a persistent, full-duplex connection allowing the server to push data instantly without a request", "HTTP is encrypted, WebSockets are not", "There is no difference"], ans: 1, exp: "WebSockets are mathematically required for real-time live chat applications and live stock tickers." }
